cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.CR 

This paper deals with the problem of identifying relevant tweets in real-time, which is a common task in natural language processing (NLP) and information retrieval (IR). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with NLP and related topics. The paper also discusses the use of machine learning models for classification, which falls under cs.IR (Information Retrieval). The paper also deals with the problem of noise in data, which is a common issue in data mining and machine learning, and could be classified under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also discusses the use of a visual analytics system, which could be classified under cs.CY (Computers and Society) or cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
